New York, NY- South-Florida artist, Hush Forte, releases his groovy self-produced single, “Greatest Fault,” today. The producer, composer, rapper, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist releases the new track as he gears up to release his full-length project, Look Closely. Hush ForteThe young lyricist prides himself on his ability to be vulnerable and transparent in his art, and the mellow yet uptempo "Greatest Fault" proves that he is only getting better with time. If you're not in a complete trance from the beat, you'll be repeating the standout lyric "the shadow never leaves his feet" – an ode to the duality of the young artists' emotions. Forte states “Growing up I learned how to hide my weaknesses. Any fears, or feelings of sadness I’d keep them tucked. I figured no one cares and the people that do care will use it against me. It wasn’t until working on this project that I learned vulnerability is a superpower. I made “Greatest Fault” when I had this realization.” Dive into his new single and get lost in a talented young artist's refreshing discovery into self. HUSH FORTE's 12-song project, Look Closely, is set to be released on October 29th and includes features from Love Mansuy, Saint Lyor, Q, Native Son, and Sophiethehomie.